<section id="calcium-score">
    <h2>Test #1: Coronary Calcium Score (CAC)</h2>

    <div class="test-card">
        <h3>The Gold Standard Screening Test</h3>
        <p><strong>What it measures:</strong> Calcium deposits in your coronary arteries (hardened plaque)</p>
        <p><strong>Cost:</strong> $75-150 (often not covered by insurance)</p>
        <p><strong>Radiation:</strong> Less than a mammogram</p>
        <p><strong>Time:</strong> 10-minute CT scan</p>

        <table class="ranges-table">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>CAC Score</th>
                    <th>What It Means</th>
                    <th>Action Required</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr class="optimal">
                    <td>0</td>
                    <td>No detectable plaque</td>
                    <td>Retest in 5 years</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="warning">
                    <td>1-99</td>
                    <td>Mild plaque burden</td>
                    <td>Aggressive prevention</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="warning">
                    <td>100-399</td>
                    <td>Moderate plaque</td>
                    <td>See cardiologist</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="danger">
                    <td>400+</td>
                    <td>Extensive disease</td>
                    <td>Immediate intervention</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>

        <p><strong>Key insight:</strong> If you have ANY calcium (score &gt; 0), you already have atherosclerosis. The goal is to stop progression.</p>
    </div>

    <h3>Understanding Progression</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Normal progression: 10-20% per year</li>
        <li>With proper treatment: 0-5% per year</li>
        <li>Track every 2-3 years if not zero</li>
        <li>Progression rate matters more than absolute number</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section id="advanced-lipids">
    <h2>Test #2: Advanced Lipid Panel</h2>

    <div class="test-card">
        <h3>Cleveland HeartLab or Similar Advanced Testing</h3>
        <p>Standard lipid panels miss the most important markers. You need particle size and inflammatory markers.</p>

        <h4>Critical Markers to Test:</h4>

        <table class="ranges-table">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Marker</th>
                    <th>Optimal</th>
                    <th>Warning</th>
                    <th>Danger</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>Small Dense LDL</strong></td>
                    <td class="optimal">&lt; 20%</td>
                    <td class="warning">20-40%</td>
                    <td class="danger">&gt; 40%</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>Oxidized LDL</strong></td>
                    <td class="optimal">&lt; 40 U/L</td>
                    <td class="warning">40-60</td>
                    <td class="danger">&gt; 60</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>ApoB</strong></td>
                    <td class="optimal">&lt; 80 mg/dL</td>
                    <td class="warning">80-100</td>
                    <td class="danger">&gt; 100</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>Lp(a)</strong></td>
                    <td class="optimal">&lt; 30 mg/dL</td>
                    <td class="warning">30-50</td>
                    <td class="danger">&gt; 50</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>HDL-P (particles)</strong></td>
                    <td class="optimal">&gt; 30 μmol/L</td>
                    <td class="warning">25-30</td>
                    <td class="danger">&lt; 25</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>

        <p><strong>Why this matters:</strong> Large fluffy LDL is harmless. Small dense LDL penetrates artery walls and oxidizes, causing plaques.</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section id="metabolic">
    <h2>Test #3: Metabolic/Insulin Panel</h2>

    <div class="test-card">
        <h3>The Tests That Catch Pre-Diabetes 10 Years Early</h3>

        <h4>Essential Metabolic Tests:</h4>

        <table class="ranges-table">
            <thead>
