        <p><strong>What elevation means:</strong> Your body is fighting something – leaky gut, hidden infection, mold exposure, or metabolic dysfunction.</p>
    </div>

    <h3>Additional Specialty Tests</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>TMAO:</strong> Gut dysbiosis marker</li>
        <li><strong>MPO (Myeloperoxidase):</strong> Vulnerable plaque marker</li>
        <li><strong>Lp-PLA2:</strong> Vascular inflammation</li>
        <li><strong>Vitamin D:</strong> Should be 50-80 ng/mL</li>
        <li><strong>Omega-3 index:</strong> Should be &gt; 8%</li>
    </ul>
</section>

